data.current_description: Publish all draft changes to the Label. Once published, the Label may not return to its draft state. See `google.apps.drive.labels.v2.Lifecycle` for more information. Publishing a Label will result in a new published revision. All previous draft revisions will be deleted. Previous published revisions will be kept but are subject to automated deletion as needed. Once published, some changes are no longer permitted. Generally, any change that would invalidate or cause new restrictions on existing metadata related to the Label will be rejected. For example, the following changes to a Label will be rejected after the Label is published: * The label cannot be directly deleted. It must be disabled first, then deleted. * Field.FieldType cannot be changed. * Changes to Field validation options cannot reject something that was previously accepted. * Reducing the max entries.
data.summary_suggestion: Publish draft label changes to production state
data.description_suggestion: Publishes all draft changes to a Label, transitioning it from draft to published state. Once published, the Label cannot return to draft state. Publishing creates a new published revision, deletes all previous draft revisions, and retains previous published revisions (subject to automated cleanup). After publishing, certain modifications are restricted: the label cannot be directly deleted (must be disabled first), field types cannot be changed, validation rules cannot become more restrictive, and maximum entry counts cannot be reduced. These restrictions prevent invalidating existing metadata associated with the label.
